Then, the next read(*, '(a)') line would read the next line. But in Java's code, after reading the integer with in.nextInt(), it reads the next line (including any remaining characters on the same line) with in.nextLine(). Wait, Java's code does:

students = in.nextInt();

in.nextLine();

Then, for each student, read a line. So in Fortran, after reading the integer, there might be remaining characters in the line (like if the input was '3  abc', but the code reads 3 and then the next line).
